Last night I was up around 2 AM just loitering around on my balcony when I saw what was either a mink or a marten (weasel-like creature, I don't think they exist in the New World) creeping under the parked cars down on the street. This is inner city - very unusual and auspicious.

First thought it was an emaciated street cat, but it was moving weird and I realized its tail was different. Someone here told me wildlife is always closer to you than you think no matter where you live and the more I ask around and hear anecdotes the more I realize he was right.

People have no idea how bad this can get. In the Russian Navy during the Russo-Japanese war and before 1917 there were entire foreign sabotage teams of spies operating capturing ships, executing the officers, blowing up ammunition, etc. It gets far worse than you can ever imagine

Imagine if American aircraft carriers started randomly exploding in ports or some nuclear submarine sank and news started appearing of Navy sailors shooting their superiors over "bad conditions" on ships. You can get one Battleship Potemkin per day. They already did it to Russia.

In the early 20th century the Russian Navy basically fell into piracy, English agents were fighting German agents, there were even still Austro-Hungarian spies operating, the admirals were corrupt and permitted all of this, the state could no longer rely on the Navy, pure horror.
